        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 6:57PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 657 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of McFaddin, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Refugio and Quintana.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 183 between mile markers 654 and 668.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 596 and 626.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
